description:
// O C C A S I O N
Me and my boyfriend went on a Tuesday evening, the place was pretty empty and it was our first time, but we weren't disappointed!

// F O O D:
- Hummus appetizer comes with an ample amount and pita, good for two. The pita is toasted well, soft on the inside and slightly crispy on the outside. Be careful, their olive isn't pitted!
- We ordered the lamb kebob, and the bazinjan tajines. The lamb is succulent and mint sauce goes nicely. If you like the sweet-garlic taste and eggplant, definitely try the latter!

// S E R V I C E:
- There was only two other tables taken during our visit. And one waitress. The food took a little longer than liked but she was lovely, and was worth the wait!

// O T H E R:
- Clean, classy environment! 
- Simple and cute presentation of food.
